TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This expression searches the input port, IN_STRING looking for the character x1A. if this character is found, a default string, VAR_DEFAULT_STRING is passed instead of the data received. At the time of this writing, NULL is the default value chosen. NOTE: This character x'1A' is the only value rejected by Teradata.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_SCRUB_HEX1A_DIM_RES_DOCUMENT

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This variable contains a single character, hex 1a. (x'1A') or decimal 026. Teradata cannot translate this character.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: VAR_HEX_1A

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This variable holds the default value that we want returned when a scrubbing operation is required.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: VAR_DEFAULT_STRING

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This port is the input string. It is set to a max 255 characters.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: IN_STRING1

TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: IN_STRING2

TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: IN_STRING3

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This port is the input string. It is set to a max 255 characters.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: IN_STRING4

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This output port contains the results of the scrubbing operation. We search for a character (x'1a') that Teradata does not accept and replace the entire port with the VAR_DEFAULT_STRING if this character is found. Otherwise the input port is passed to the output port.
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION_DESCRIPTION: This port checks to see if a target character (hex '1A') represented as a variable for the sake of clarity and then outputs a default value also represented as a variable if the character is found or outputs the input string if the value is not found.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: OUT_STRING1

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Surrogated Key of the reservation Number.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RES_ID

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: System Identification Number. It identifies the system this reservation came from.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: SYSTEM_ID

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Brand identification Number.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: BRAND_ID

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This is the reservation number that the customer was assigned to.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RESERVATION_CD

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Creation date of the Reservation. When the reservation is created this date is set and does not change.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RESERVATION_CREATE_DT

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Reservation Last Modified Date
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RES_LAST_MODIFY_DT

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Any comment on a res transaction.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RES_NOTES

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Date/Time field that stores the reservation projected Check Out (rent) date.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RES_PROJ_CO_DT

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Date/Time field that stores the reservation projected check in(return).
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RES_PROJ_CI_DT

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Last Name of the person that is reserving the car.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: LAST_NAME

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: First Name of the customer that is reserving the car.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: FIRST_NAME

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Flight Number associated with this reservation.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: FLIGHT_NBR

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Represents the last time the information was updated or loaded into the data warehouse.
TARGETFIELD.NAME: LOAD_TS

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: European Reservation number - Alamo only
TARGETFIELD.NAME: EURO_RESNUM

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: National only. - Special instructions to rent agents. Odyssey: From table RES_SPCL_INSTRS, concatenation of fields INSTR_LN1 INSTR_LN2 INSTR_LN3
TARGETFIELD.NAME: SPCL_INSTRS

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Rental Agreement number assigned to a checked out Reservation
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RENT_DOC_CD

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Email address of the reservation customer, the address to which the confirmation email is sent. Odyssey: RES_CLR_INFO.CLR_EMAIL_ADDR
TARGETFIELD.NAME: CALLER_EMAIL

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Email address of the travel agent or tour operator who made a reservation on behalf of the end customer. Odyssey: RES_CLR_INFO.AGENT_EMAIL_ADDRESS
TARGETFIELD.NAME: AGENT_EMAIL

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Caller who made the reservation. Odyssey: RES.CLR_NAME
TARGETFIELD.NAME: CALLER_NAME

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Premium Tour Products Flag
TARGETFIELD.NAME: PTP_ELIGIBLE_FLG

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Record Indicator ODY source is GWYDB.RES.PRN_RCD_LOC
TARGETFIELD.NAME: RECORD_LOCATOR

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: External reference number associated to reservation (usually same as the Euro_Resnum) Source is GWYDB.RES.EXTRNL_REF
TARGETFIELD.NAME: EXTERNAL_REFERENCE_CD

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: External Voucher number when the MOP is voucher. Source is GWYDB.RES.EXTRNL_VCHR_ID
TARGETFIELD.NAME: VOUCHER_CD

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Search Engine Marketing Keyword
TARGETFIELD.NAME: SEM_KEYWORD

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Search Engine Marketing Click timestamp
TARGETFIELD.NAME: SEM_CLICK_TMSP

TARGETFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Search Engine Marketing Conversion timestamp
TARGETFIELD.NAME: SEM_CONVERSION_TMSP
